- Instance should have a Linux OS
- Instance should be launched with most recent patches

1) Name & Tags
Label you can assign to an AWS resource
Consists of Key and Value
Benefits: Filtering, cost allocation

2) Choose an AMI
- Template that consists of O/S (Windows/Linux),
Applications, Launch permissions
--Choose an AMI according to the use of your instance
is it a web server? Application server?
--You can't change an AMI after creation

3) Instance Type
Specifies the hardware used. i.e) CPU, RAM(memory),
disk space, Network performance
--Instances types for light, heavy & extreme workloads
-- Higher generation more powerful

Instance categories: 
a) General- t2, t3
b) Compute optimized- high performance processors (c4,c5)
c) Memory optimized (R4, R5)
--can be changed after launcing the instance
--Option of vertical scaling (Scale up or down for CPU)

4) Key pair - Security credentials you used toprove your identity when connecvting to the AWs resource
Consists of Public key that AWS stores
Private key that you store
-Can't be added after launch
windows -RDP
Linux instance- SSH

5)Network Settings
- VPC
- Subnet
- Security Group to place your instance

REGION- assumed using the management console your working on

6) Security Group (stateful)--instance level
- Virtual firewall for your instances
- Specifies allow rules but not deny rules

Use the VM to host your website.
in terminal:

sudo su -> Root admin

yum update -y

yum install -y httpd ->instal Apache service- downloads all packages- web server

systemctl status httpd (Shows inactive)- show https status
systemctl enable httpd enable httpd
system start httpd  httpd server is now up and website accessible 

mkdir temp --> Create Directory --Template

wget ziplinkfreefile -->((Download website)To access free websites) (https://www.free-css.com/assets/files/free-css-templates/download/page296/oxer.zip)
ls (oxer.zip)

unzip oxer.zip (unzip file)

cd oxer-html (See all styling)

Convert server into web server

mv * /var/www/html/  Convert server into web server

cd /var/www/html/
Use public IP to access website

